     */
    public interface IEntryPoint extends IObject
    {
        /**
         * This method shall be called when an associated event is emitted.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IEntryPoint.Execute
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def void Execute()
    }

    /**
     * This is an enumeration of the available states of the simulator. The Setup phase is split into three different states, the Execution phase has five different states, and the Termination phase has two states.
     *
     * @uuid da4b5c6f-f9af-389c-be25-b1b8dc93dd29
     * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind
     */
    public enum SimulatorStateKind
    {
        /**
         * In Building state, the component hierarchy is created. This is done by an external component, not by the simulator.
         * This state is entered automatically after the simulation environment has performed its initialisation.
         * In this state, Publish() and Configure() can be called any time to call the corresponding Publish() and Configure() operations of each component.
         * This state is left with the Connect() state transition method.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Building
         */
        SSK_Building = 0,
        /**
         * In Connecting state, the simulation environment traverses the component hierarchy and calls the Connect() method of each component.
         * This state is entered using the Connect() state transition.
         * After connecting all components to the simulator, an automatic state transition to the Initialising state is performed.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Connecting
         */
        SSK_Connecting = 1,
        /**
         * In Initialising state, the simulation environment executes all initialisation entry points in the order they have been added to the simulator using the AddInitEntryPoint() method.
         * This state is either entered automatically after the simulation environment has connected all models to the simulator, or manually from Standby state using the Initialise() state transition.
         * After calling all initialisation entry points, an automatic state transition to the Standby state is performed.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Initialising
         */
        SSK_Initialising = 2,
        /**
         * In Standby state, the simulation environment (namely the Time Keeper Service) does not progress simulation time. Only entry points registered relative to Zulu time are executed.
         * This state is entered automatically from the Initialising, Storing, and Restoring states, or manually from the Executing state using the Hold() state transition.
         * This state is left with one of the Run(), Store(), Restore(), Initialise(), Reconnect() or Exit() state transitions.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Standby
         */
        SSK_Standby = 3,
        /**
         * In Executing state, the simulation environment (namely the Time Keeper Service) does progress simulation time. Entry points registered with any of the available time kinds are executed.
         * This state is entered using the Run() state transition.
         * This state is left using the Hold() state transition.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Executing
         */
        SSK_Executing = 4,
        /**
         * In Storing state, the simulation environment first stores the values of all fields published with the State attribute to storage (typically a file). Afterwards, the Store() method of all components (Models and Services) implementing the optional IPersist interface is called, to allow custom storing of additional information. While in this state, fields published with the State attribute must not be modified by the models, to ensure that a consistent set of field values is stored.
         * This state is entered using the Store() state transition.
         * After storing the simulator state, an automatic state transition to the Standby state is performed.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Storing
         */
        SSK_Storing = 5,
        /**
         * In Restoring state, the simulation environment first restores the values of all fields published with the State attribute from storage. Afterwards, the Restore() method of all components implementing the optional IPersist interface is called, to allow custom restoring of additional information. While in this state, fields published with the State attribute must not be modified by the models, to ensure that a consistent set of field values is restored.
         * This state is entered using the Restore() state transition.
         * After restoring the simulator state, an automatic state transition to the Standby state is performed.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Restoring
         */
        SSK_Restoring = 6,
        /**
         * In Reconnecting state, the simulation environment makes sure that models that have been added to the simulator after leaving the Building state are properly published, configured and connected.
         * This state is entered using the Reconnect() state transition.
         * After connecting all new models, an automatic state transition to the Standby state is performed.
         *
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1201788190327_911770_1965
         */
        SSK_Reconnecting = 7,
        /**
         * In Exiting state, the simulation environment is properly terminating a running simulation.
         * This state is entered using the Exit() state transition. After exiting, the simulator is in an undefined state.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Exiting
         */
        SSK_Exiting = 8,
        /**
         * In this state, the simulation environment performs an abnormal simulation shut-down.
         * This state is entered using the Abort() state transition. After aborting, the simulator is in an undefined state.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimulatorStateKind.SSK_Aborting
         */
        SSK_Aborting = 9
    }

    /**
     * An entry point collection is an ordered collection of entry points, which allows iterating all members.
     *
     * @uuid dfa88aea-fc86-39b9-955a-cda6b69296e6
     * @type ICollection&lt;Smp::IEntryPoint&gt;
     * @namespace Smp
     * @location Smp/ICollection.h,Smp/IEntryPoint.h
     * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.EntryPointCollection
     */
    public native EntryPointCollection

    /**
     * This interface gives access to the simulation environment state and state transitions. Further, it provides convenience methods to add models, and to add and retrieve simulation services.
     *
     * @uuid 4ba4ca88-e707-3e9e-ba62-bab8e03846f4
     * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator
     */
    public interface ISimulator extends IComposite
    {
        /**
         * Name of the model container.
         *
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1199981191857_588268_6728
         */
        @Attributes.Static
        constant String8 SMP_SimulatorModels = "Models"

        /**
         * Name of the service container.
         *
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1199981210210_369427_6733
         */
        @Attributes.Static
        constant String8 SMP_SimulatorServices = "Services"

        /**
         * This method asks the simulation environment to call all initialisation entry points again.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Initialise
         */
        def void Initialise() throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method asks the simulation environment to call the Publish() method of all service and model instances in the component hierarchy which are still in Created state.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Publish
         */
        def void Publish() throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method asks the simulation environment to call the Configure() method of all service and model instances which are still in Publishing state.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Configure
         */
        def void Configure() throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method informs the simulation environment that the hierarchy of model instances has been configured, and can now be connected to the simulator. Thus, the simulation environment calls the Connect() method of all service and model instances.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Connect
         */
        def void Connect() throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method changes from Standby to Executing state.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Run
         */
        def void Run() throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method changes from Executing to Standby state.
         *
         * @param immediate True if the simulator shall stop immediately after completion of the current scheduler event, false if the simulator shall still process all events of the current simulation time before entering Standby state.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Hold
         */
        def void Hold(in Bool immediate) throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method is used to store a state vector to file.
         *
         * @param filename Name including the full path to use for simulation state vector file.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Store
         */
        def void Store(in String8 filename) throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method is used to restore a state vector from file.
         *
         * @param filename Name including the full path of simulation state vector file.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Restore
         */
        def void Restore(in String8 filename) throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method asks the simulation environment to reconnect the component hierarchy starting at the given root component.
         *
         * @param root Root component to start reconnecting from. This can be the parent component of a newly added model. To reconnect all models under the simulator, use nullptr (as the simulator is no component).
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1201789543204_487813_2065
         */
        def void Reconnect(inout IComponent root) throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method is used for a normal termination of a simulation.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Exit
         */
        def void Exit() throws InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method is used for an abnormal termination of a simulation.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.Abort
         */
        def void Abort()

        /**
         * Return the current simulator state.
         *
         * @return Current simulator state.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.GetState
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def SimulatorStateKind ReturnParameter GetState()

        /**
         * This method can be used to add entry points that shall be executed in the Initialising state.
         * If the simulation is in Building, Connecting or Standby state, it adds the entry point to the list of entry points to be executed once the simulation reaches Initialising state.
         * If the simulation is not in Building, Connecting or Standby state, then it returns and no action is taken.
         * This allows components to subscribe to a callback during initialization phase since there are only explicit methods defined for Publish, Configure and Connect. This choice is taken since most models require actions to be taken in Publish, Configure and Connect, however only a minority require to perform some actions during initialization.
         * The ownership of the entry point remains with the caller.
         *
         * @param entryPoint Entry point to execute in Initialising state.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.AddInitEntryPoint
         */
        def void AddInitEntryPoint(inout IEntryPoint entryPoint)

        /**
         * This method adds a model to the models collection of the simulator, i.e. to the "Models" container.
         *
         * @param model New model to add to collection of root models, i.e. to the "Models" container. The ownership of the model is handed over to the object implementing ISimulator.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.AddModel
         */
        def void AddModel(inout IModel model) throws DuplicateName, InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * This method adds a user-defined service to the services collection, i.e. to the "Services" container.
         *
         * @param service Service to add to collection of services, i.e. to the "Services" container. The ownership of the service is handed over to the object implementing ISimulator.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.AddService
         */
        def void AddService(inout IService service) throws DuplicateName, InvalidSimulatorState

        /**
         * Query for a service component by its name.
         *
         * @param name Service name.
         * @return Service with the given name, or nullptr if no service with the given name could be found.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.GetService
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def IService ReturnParameter GetService(in String8 name)

        /**
         * Return interface to logger service.
         *
         * @return Interface to mandatory logger service.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.GetLogger
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Services.ILogger ReturnParameter GetLogger()

        /**
         * Return interface to time keeper service.
         *
         * @return Interface to mandatory time keeper service.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.GetTimeKeeper
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Services.ITimeKeeper ReturnParameter GetTimeKeeper()

        /**
         * Return interface to scheduler service.
         *
         * @return Interface to mandatory scheduler service.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.GetScheduler
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Services.IScheduler ReturnParameter GetScheduler()

        /**
         * Return interface to event manager service.
         *
         * @return Interface to mandatory event manager service.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.ISimulator.GetEventManager
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Services.IEventManager ReturnParameter GetEventManager()

        /**
         * Return interface to resolver service.
         *
         * @return Interface to mandatory resolver service.
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1200048954445_807180_3876
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Services.IResolver ReturnParameter GetResolver()

        /**
         * Return interface to link registry service.
         *
         * @return Interface to mandatory link registry service.
         * @id _12_1_f810373_1203672796165_291778_1649
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Services.ILinkRegistry ReturnParameter GetLinkRegistry()

        /**
         * This method registers a component factory with the simulator. The simulator can use this factory to create component instances of the component implementation in its CreateInstance() method.
         * The memory management of the factory is passed to the simulator, who is in charge of deleting the factory at the exiting or aborting state.
         *
         * @param componentFactory Factory to create instance of the component implementation.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IDynamicSimulator.RegisterFactory
         */
        def void RegisterFactory(inout IFactory componentFactory) throws DuplicateUuid

        /**
         * This method creates an instance of the component with the given unique identifier.
         *
         * @param uuid Unique identifier of the component to create.
         * @param name Name of the new instance. If the name provided is not a valid object name, an exception of type InvalidObjectName is raised.
         * @param description Description of the new instance.
         * @param parent Parent object of the new instance.
         * @return New instance of the component with the given unique identifier or nullptr in case no factory for the given unique identifier has been registered.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IDynamicSimulator.CreateInstance
         */
        def IComponent ReturnParameter CreateInstance(in Uuid uuid, in String8 name, in String8 description, inout IComposite parent) throws InvalidObjectName

        /**
         * This method returns the factory of the component with the given unique identifier.
         *
         * @param uuid Unique identifier of the component to get the factory for.
         * @return Factory of the component with the given unique identifier or nullptr in case no factory for the given unique identifier has been registered.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IDynamicSimulator.GetFactory
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def IFactory ReturnParameter GetFactory(in Uuid uuid)

        /**
         * This method returns all factories that have been registered with the simulator.
         *
         * @return Collection of factories.
         * @id _17_0_2_5_f810373_1567285666557_257495_11210
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def @Attributes.ByPointer @Attributes.Const FactoryCollection ReturnParameter GetFactories()

        /**
         * Give access to the global type registry.
         *
         * @return Reference to global type registry.
         * @id _17_0_2_5_f810373_1567287068354_307373_11269
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Publication.ITypeRegistry ReturnParameter GetTypeRegistry()

        /**
         * This operation loads a library of a package into memory.
         * At loading time, the Initialise() function of this library will be called.
         * At exiting or aborting time, the Finalise() function of this library will be called.
         *
         * @param libraryPath Path to the library to load.
        This needs to be a valid path name given the constraints of the operating system.
         * @param flag Loading flag for the library, to define in which scope the symbols from the library are made available.
         * @id _17_0_2_5_f810373_1567287129553_172735_11275
         */
        def void LoadLibrary(in String8 libraryPath, in LibraryLoadingFlag flag = LibraryLoadingFlag.LLF_Auto) throws FileNotFound, InvalidFile, InvalidSmpVersion
    }

    /**
     * Interface for a component factory.
     *
     * @uuid 77c7e2d6-f64e-30d6-979f-72ba29f8860b
     * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IFactory
     */
    public interface IFactory extends IObject
    {
        /**
         * Get Universally unique identifier of the type instantiated by the factory.
         *
         * @return Universally unique identifier of component.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IFactory.GetSpecification
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Uuid ReturnParameter GetUuid()

        /**
         * Returns the fully qualified C++ name of the type.
         *
         * @return Fully qualified C++ name of type that is created by this factory.
         * @id _17_0_2_5_f810373_1567286642628_520205_11263
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def String8 ReturnParameter GetTypeName()

        /**
         * Create a new instance with given name, description and parent.
         *
         * @param name Name of the new instance.
        If the name provided is not a valid object name, an exception of type InvalidObjectName is raised.
         * @param description Description of the new instance.
         * @param parent Parent object of the new instance.
         * @return New component instance.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IFactory.CreateInstance
         */
        def IComponent ReturnParameter CreateInstance(in String8 name, in String8 description, inout IComposite parent) throws InvalidObjectName

        /**
         * Delete an existing instance.
         *
         * @param instance Instance to delete.
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IFactory.DeleteInstance
         */
        def void DeleteInstance(inout IComponent instance)
    }

    /**
     * A factory collection is an ordered collection of factories, which allows iterating all members.
     *
     * @uuid 60b72882-d7a1-37d4-96fd-2ad28b7fb0e2
     * @type ICollection&lt;Smp::IFactory&gt;
     * @namespace Smp
     * @location Smp/ICollection.h,Smp/IFactory.h
     * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.FactoryCollection
     */
    public native FactoryCollection

    /**
     * Interface that provides functionality to allow publishing members, including fields, properties and operations.
     *
     * @uuid a7070d40-b59c-3d00-940b-91618fde21b6
     * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.IPublication
     */
    public interface IPublication extends Smp.Publication.IPublishField
    {
        /**
         * Publish an operation with the given name, description and view kind.
         * If an Operation with the same name has not been published, this creates a new IPublishOperation instance and returns it.
         * If an Operations with the same name has already been published, this will update the “description” and “view”  of the previous publication, clears all published Parameters for the Operation, and returns the same IPublishOperation of the previously published Operation.
         * If an object with the same name has been published before, and it is not an Operation, an exception of type DuplicateName is thrown.
         * It the component being published does not implement IDynamicInvocation, an exception of type NoDynamicInvocation is thrown.
         *
         * @param name Name of operation.
         * @param description Description of operation.
         * @param view View kind of operation node in simulation tree.
         * @return Reference to the operation that has been created, to publish parameters against.
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1204812654054_628396_3660
         */
        def Smp.Publication.IPublishOperation ReturnParameter PublishOperation(in String8 name, in String8 description, in ViewKind view = ViewKind.VK_All) throws InvalidObjectName, DuplicateName, NoDynamicInvocation

        /**
         * Publish an operation defined internally that implements the IOperation interface.
         * If an Operations with the same name has already been published, this will replace that operation with this one.
         * If an object with the same name has been published before, and it is not an Operation, an exception of type DuplicateName is thrown.
         * It the component being published does not implement IDynamicInvocation, an exception of type NoDynamicInvocation is thrown.
         *
         * @param operation Operation to publish.
         * @id _2021x_2_126903bf_1724846371344_386552_3818
         */
        def void PublishOperation(inout IOperation operation) throws DuplicateName, NoDynamicInvocation

        /**
         * Publish a property with the given name, description and view kind.
         * If a Property with the same name has not been published, this creates a new IProperty instance and returns it.
         * If a Property with the same name has already been published, this will update the “description” , “view”, "access", and "type"  of the previous publication, and returns the same IProperty of the previously published Property.
         * If an object with the same name has been published before, and it is not a Property, an exception of type DuplicateName is thrown.
         * It the component being published does not implement IDynamicInvocation, an exception of type NoDynamicInvocation is thrown.
         * It the primitive type kind of the publication type is None, it throws an exception of type InvalidType.
         *
         * @param name Property name.
         * @param description Property description.
         * @param typeUuid Uuid of type of property.
         * @param accessKind Access kind of Property.
         * @param view Show field in model tree.
         * @return Reference to the property that has been generated by the publication call.
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1204812838810_250494_3675
         */
        def IProperty ReturnParameter PublishProperty(in String8 name, in String8 description, in Uuid typeUuid, in AccessKind accessKind, in ViewKind view = ViewKind.VK_All) throws Smp.Publication.TypeNotRegistered, InvalidObjectName, DuplicateName, NoDynamicInvocation, InvalidType

        /**
         * Publish a property defined internally that implements the IProperty interface.
         * If a Property with the same name has already been published, this will replace that property with this one.
         * If an object with the same name has been published before, and it is not a Property, an exception of type DuplicateName is thrown.
         * It the component being published does not implement IDynamicInvocation, an exception of type NoDynamicInvocation is thrown.
         *
         * @param property Property to publish.
         * @id _2021x_2_126903bf_1724846269778_544611_3814
         */
        def void PublishProperty(inout IProperty property) throws DuplicateName, NoDynamicInvocation

        /**
         * Get the property of given name.
         *
         * @param name Property name.
         * @return Instance of property for given name, or nullptr if no property exists with the given name.
         * @id _2021x_2_126903bf_1724922065694_494348_5372
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def IProperty ReturnParameter GetProperty(in String8 name)

        /**
         * Provides the collection of properties that have been published.
         *
         * @return Collection of properties that have been published, which may be empty.
         * @id _17_0_2_5_f810373_1570606784640_841832_10248
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def @Attributes.ByPointer @Attributes.Const PropertyCollection ReturnParameter GetProperties()

        /**
         * Get the operation of given name.
         *
         * @param name Operation name.
         * @return Instance of operation for given name, or nullptr if no operation exists with the given name.
         * @id _2021x_2_126903bf_1724922199126_45154_5384
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def IOperation ReturnParameter GetOperation(in String8 name)

        /**
         * Provides the collection of operations that have been published.
         *
         * @return Collection of operations that have been published, which may be empty.
         * @id _17_0_2_5_f810373_1570606784640_879836_10249
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def @Attributes.ByPointer @Attributes.Const OperationCollection ReturnParameter GetOperations()

        /**
         * Give access to the global type registry.
         *
         * @return Reference to global type registry.
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1204801000859_21347_2895
         */
        @Attributes.Const
        def Smp.Publication.ITypeRegistry ReturnParameter GetTypeRegistry()

        /**
         * Call this operation to release all data created during earlier Publish calls to this instance.
         * This invalidated all pointers retrieved earlier via this instance.
         *
         * @id _17_0_2_5_f810373_1567286888186_220549_11267
         */
        def void Unpublish()
    }

    /**
     * This is an enumeration of the available primitive types.
     *
     * @uuid 0aefd3d3-d00a-35a7-bf42-4bfacb538dec
     * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind
     */
    public enum PrimitiveTypeKind
    {
        /**
         * No type, e.g. for void.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_None
         */
        PTK_None = 0,
        /**
         * 8 bit character type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Char8
         */
        PTK_Char8 = 1,
        /**
         * Boolean with true and false.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Bool
         */
        PTK_Bool = 2,
        /**
         * 8 bit signed integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Int8
         */
        PTK_Int8 = 3,
        /**
         * 8 bit unsigned integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_UInt8
         */
        PTK_UInt8 = 4,
        /**
         * 16 bit signed integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Int16
         */
        PTK_Int16 = 5,
        /**
         * 16 bit unsigned integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_UInt16
         */
        PTK_UInt16 = 6,
        /**
         * 32 bit signed integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Int32
         */
        PTK_Int32 = 7,
        /**
         * 32 bit unsigned integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_UInt32
         */
        PTK_UInt32 = 8,
        /**
         * 64 bit signed integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Int64
         */
        PTK_Int64 = 9,
        /**
         * 64 bit unsigned integer type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_UInt64
         */
        PTK_UInt64 = 10,
        /**
         * 32 bit single-precision floating-point type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Float32
         */
        PTK_Float32 = 11,
        /**
         * 64 bit double-precision floating-point type.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Float64
         */
        PTK_Float64 = 12,
        /**
         * Duration in nanoseconds.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_Duration
         */
        PTK_Duration = 13,
        /**
         * Absolute time in nanoseconds.
         *
         * @id _smp2_Smp.xml_Smp.SimpleTypeKind.ST_DateTime
         */
        PTK_DateTime = 14,
        /**
         * 8 bit character string.
         *
         * @id _12_1_910029a_1200056796049_642892_3988
         */
        PTK_String8 = 15
    }

    /**
     * Array of AnySimple values.
     *
     * @uuid 7a49b2e1-8727-33b0-9166-47b5ea21b061
     * @type AnySimple*
     * @namespace Smp
